[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating dynamic class tests**\n\nI’m thinking about dynamic class tests and the rule that says each one should have its own dedicated Java test file. The existing EndpointClassHolder/PojoClassHolder might refer to inner holder classes, but their coverage report shows no activity. I'm questioning whether these holders are even being counted since they call the same WsWebSocketContainer. I wonder if the tests aren’t being executed properly. Maybe the dynamic-access coverage isn’t set up right due to how the tests are compiled.\n\n**Analyzing dynamic coverage**\n\nI think dynamic coverage might come from matching native image build-time reports with generated metadata config, rather than during agent runtime. It seems like it doesn’t reflect on test target classes since the metadata for tests is under generated test resources. I wonder if adding tests that successfully connect to a real local WebSocket server could help. If an invalid \"http\" path throws exceptions before entering instrumented methods, then that could be an issue. Lastly, I need to check dependencies for the local embedded Tomcat websocket server.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_073bb084c64aa19e0169fce6cd317881a0b225715c25d2bb88\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp_ObUWeuuzPLJfx5nI1bbYv4p_Y9JCAKU62ASBSpzLHTDhXZOHFHNnB84cFgjUENX9PErs4JbBJr8Z2tlOeY2COgbVSt5jG4Ru2GGHNglUwfowgqj00MfW0vyWbnVkNS3IubCUAvn2OFzYFa5RCKQ6Fp6nYdPQmaNwpK8z1HMCVO8DEJTJveu2Waqksi_f72Nntf1UYoe1P2Q0WJMhZ2kdpqYTnmplfLDavZYSk1iae3ajwkbpAIldX_UPMT72DfSAq3z3H3ZoNhm3y2G2lukRRdkUvvBgxOhJNfkkuzzYY7rM7aH4hIkmrmCgHyilaVmIVH3nrivkNaWtFHvWPRwGq6_-1Hu_TebVM_FjsDZmm-6AU_N63xuZLdoSOSkig0GlPdTtrjEZwU3TDphQ9oMBhTPrzqBcBW2utedofRLhWpW-ToEdVBHoNBZ85__jpNPlzw9MBPHKi0viMyp0VLwjS0UQn_wsRCBn_jOgoQo3pKIU3BOp32EFm4lHML4s9lNbATl4laJCwcAJQ9Og4Lqvidnsvo5z1b6bwMfMORTs3qPtCb1J4gYQKzmi8YSUrZ-Mkuw2uq-z6JZfgeluWy3dnwrwDTUy0ELyccmf